OL,3,CEngland's only Balalaika orchestra
OL,4,Cissues plea for new members
OL,6,FKalinka in Chorlton is England's only
OL,7,FBalalaika orchestra. Founded in 1984,
OL,8,Fit's the only musical group of its
OL,9,Fkind in the UK and is on the hunt for
OL,10,Fnew members.
OL,12,FFounder Brian Hulme, 82, leads a group
OL,13,Fof 20 musicians, the youngest aged
OL,14,Fjust nine years old, who meet weekly.
OL,16,FFamously used on Kate Bush's track
OL,17,FRunning Up That Hill, the instrument
OL,18,Fhas an enduring appeal but Brian is
OL,19,Fconcerned that if new members don't
OL,20,Fjoin, Kalinka may disappear.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/5
