OL,3,CEngland's only Balalaika orchestra
OL,4,Cissues plea for new members
OL,6,FHe says it's important to separate the
OL,7,Fcountry's arts and music from its
OL,8,Fpolitics, and simply enjoy the unique
OL,9,Fsound of the Balalaika and its oval
OL,10,Fshaped cousin the Domra.
OL,12,FHe said: "It's a very simple
OL,13,Finstrument and simple to learn. To get
OL,14,Fonto more sophisticated stuff is quite
OL,15,Fdifficult!"
OL,17,FA group member said: "it's a lovely
OL,18,FEastern European instrument. I have
OL,19,Froots in Lithuania so I find that
OL,20,Fquite interesting."
